{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Like many of you here, I am trying to contribute"},{"time":6000,"text":"towards a renaissance in Africa."},{"time":9000,"text":"The question of transformation in Africa"},{"time":11000,"text":"really is a question of leadership."},{"time":13000,"text":"Africa can only be transformed by enlightened leaders."},{"time":18000,"text":"And it is my contention that the manner in which"},{"time":20000,"text":"we educate our leaders is fundamental"},{"time":24000,"text":"to progress on this continent."},{"time":28000,"text":"I want to tell you some stories that explain my view."},{"time":33000,"text":"We all heard about the importance of stories yesterday."},{"time":37000,"text":"An American friend of mine this year volunteered as a nurse in Ghana,"},{"time":42000,"text":"and in a period of three months she came to a conclusion"},{"time":45000,"text":"about the state of leadership in Africa"},{"time":48000,"text":"that had taken me over a decade to reach."},{"time":51000,"text":"Twice she was involved in surgeries"},{"time":54000,"text":"where they lost power at the hospital."},{"time":59000,"text":"The emergency generators did not start."},{"time":62000,"text":"There was not a flashlight, not a lantern, not a candle --"},{"time":67000,"text":"pitch black."},{"time":68000,"text":"The patient's cut open, twice."},{"time":73000,"text":"The first time it was a C-section."},{"time":77000,"text":"Thankfully, baby was out -- mother and child survived."}]},{"cues":[{"time":82000,"text":"The second time was a procedure that involved local anesthesia."},{"time":87000,"text":"Anesthetic wears off. The patient feels pain."},{"time":90000,"text":"He's crying. He's screaming. He's praying."},{"time":95000,"text":"Pitch black. Not a candle, not a flashlight."},{"time":101000,"text":"And that hospital could have afforded flashlights."},{"time":105000,"text":"They could have afforded to purchase these things, but they didn't."},{"time":109000,"text":"And it happened twice."},{"time":111000,"text":"Another time, she watched in horror as nurses watched a patient die"},{"time":117000,"text":"because they refused to give her oxygen that they had."},{"time":123000,"text":"And so three months later,"},{"time":125000,"text":"just before she returned to the United States,"},{"time":128000,"text":"nurses in Accra go on strike."},{"time":130000,"text":"And her recommendation is"},{"time":133000,"text":"take this opportunity to fire everyone, start all over again."},{"time":137000,"text":"Start all over again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139000,"text":"Now what does this have to do with leadership?"},{"time":144000,"text":"You see, the folks at the ministry of health,"},{"time":149000,"text":"the hospital administrators, the doctors, the nurses --"},{"time":155000,"text":"they are among just five percent of their peers"},{"time":159000,"text":"who get an education after secondary school."},{"time":163000,"text":"They are the elite. They are our leaders."},{"time":167000,"text":"Their decisions, their actions matter."},{"time":170000,"text":"And when they fail, a nation literally suffers."},{"time":175000,"text":"So when I speak of leadership,"},{"time":177000,"text":"I'm not talking about just political leaders."},{"time":181000,"text":"We've heard a lot about that."},{"time":183000,"text":"I'm talking about the elite."},{"time":187000,"text":"Those who've been trained,"},{"time":189000,"text":"whose job it is to be the guardians of their society."},{"time":194000,"text":"The lawyers, the judges, the policemen, the doctors,"},{"time":198000,"text":"the engineers, the civil servants --"},{"time":202000,"text":"those are the leaders."},{"time":204000,"text":"And we need to train them right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207000,"text":"Now, my first pointed and memorable experience with leadership in Ghana"},{"time":213000,"text":"occurred when I was 16 years old."},{"time":215000,"text":"We had just had a military coup,"},{"time":217000,"text":"and soldiers were pervasive in our society."},{"time":220000,"text":"They were a pervasive presence."},{"time":222000,"text":"And one day I go to the airport to meet my father,"},{"time":225000,"text":"and as I walk up this grassy slope from the car park"},{"time":228000,"text":"to the terminal building,"},{"time":231000,"text":"I'm stopped by two soldiers wielding AK-47 assault weapons."},{"time":236000,"text":"And they asked me to join a crowd of people"},{"time":240000,"text":"that were running up and down this embankment."},{"time":244000,"text":"Why? Because the path I had taken was considered out of bounds."},{"time":250000,"text":"No sign to this effect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253000,"text":"Now, I was 16. I was very worried about"},{"time":257000,"text":"what my peers at school might think"},{"time":259000,"text":"if they saw me running up and down this hill."},{"time":261000,"text":"I was especially concerned of what the girls might think."},{"time":266000,"text":"And so I started to argue with these men."},{"time":268000,"text":"It was a little reckless, but you know, I was 16."},{"time":270000,"text":"I got lucky."},{"time":272000,"text":"A Ghana Airways pilot falls into the same predicament."},{"time":276000,"text":"Because of his uniform they speak to him differently,"},{"time":278000,"text":"and they explain to him that they're just following orders."},{"time":281000,"text":"So he takes their radio, talks to their boss,"},{"time":284000,"text":"and gets us all released."},{"time":286000,"text":"What lessons would you take from an experience like this?"},{"time":289000,"text":"Several, for me."},{"time":291000,"text":"Leadership matters. Those men are following"},{"time":294000,"text":"the orders of a superior officer."},{"time":298000,"text":"I learned something about courage."},{"time":300000,"text":"It was important not to look at those guns."},{"time":304000,"text":"And I also learned that it can be helpful to think about girls."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":310000,"text":"So a few years after this event, I leave Ghana on a scholarship"},{"time":316000,"text":"to go to Swarthmore College for my education."},{"time":319000,"text":"It was a breath of fresh air."},{"time":322000,"text":"You know, the faculty there didn't want us to memorize information"},{"time":327000,"text":"and repeat back to them as I was used to back in Ghana."},{"time":331000,"text":"They wanted us to think critically."},{"time":333000,"text":"They wanted us to be analytical."},{"time":335000,"text":"They wanted us to be concerned about social issues."},{"time":339000,"text":"In my economics classes I got high marks"},{"time":342000,"text":"for my understanding of basic economics."},{"time":345000,"text":"But I learned something more profound than that,"},{"time":348000,"text":"which is that the leaders -- the managers of Ghana's economy --"},{"time":355000,"text":"were making breathtakingly bad decisions"},{"time":358000,"text":"that had brought our economy to the brink of collapse."},{"time":362000,"text":"And so here was this lesson again -- leadership matters."},{"time":365000,"text":"It matters a great deal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368000,"text":"But I didn't really fully understand what had happened to me at Swarthmore."},{"time":372000,"text":"I had an inkling,"},{"time":375000,"text":"but I didn't fully realize it until I went out into the workplace"},{"time":379000,"text":"and I went to work at Microsoft Corporation."},{"time":383000,"text":"And I was part of this team -- this thinking, learning team"},{"time":388000,"text":"whose job it was to design and implement new software"},{"time":393000,"text":"that created value in the world."},{"time":396000,"text":"And it was brilliant to be part of this team."},{"time":399000,"text":"It was brilliant."},{"time":401000,"text":"And I realized just what had happened to me at Swarthmore,"},{"time":405000,"text":"this transformation --"},{"time":407000,"text":"the ability to confront problems, complex problems,"},{"time":412000,"text":"and to design solutions to those problems."},{"time":415000,"text":"The ability to create is the most empowering thing"},{"time":419000,"text":"that can happen to an individual."},{"time":421000,"text":"And I was part of that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424000,"text":"Now, while I was at Microsoft, the annual revenues of that company"},{"time":429000,"text":"grew larger than the GDP of the Republic of Ghana."},{"time":434000,"text":"And by the way, it's continued to."},{"time":437000,"text":"The gap has widened since I left."},{"time":441000,"text":"Now, I've already spoken about one of the reasons why this has occurred."},{"time":445000,"text":"I mean, it's the people there who are so hardworking,"},{"time":448000,"text":"persistent, creative, empowered."},{"time":454000,"text":"But there were also some external factors:"},{"time":457000,"text":"free markets, the rule of law, infrastructure."},{"time":462000,"text":"These things were provided by institutions"},{"time":466000,"text":"run by the people that I call leaders."},{"time":470000,"text":"And those leaders did not emerge spontaneously."},{"time":473000,"text":"Somebody trained them to do the work that they do."},{"time":478000,"text":"Now, while I was at Microsoft, this funny thing happened."},{"time":480000,"text":"I became a parent."},{"time":482000,"text":"And for the first time, Africa mattered more to me than ever before."},{"time":487000,"text":"Because I realized that the state of the African continent"},{"time":491000,"text":"would matter to my children and their children."},{"time":495000,"text":"That the state of the world -- the state of the world"},{"time":501000,"text":"depends on what's happening to Africa,"},{"time":506000,"text":"as far as my kids would be concerned."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508000,"text":"And at this time, when I was going through"},{"time":512000,"text":"what I call my \"pre-mid-life crisis,\""},{"time":516000,"text":"Africa was a mess."},{"time":518000,"text":"Somalia had disintegrated into anarchy."},{"time":520000,"text":"Rwanda was in the throes of this genocidal war."},{"time":524000,"text":"And it seemed to me that that was the wrong direction,"},{"time":526000,"text":"and I needed to be back helping."},{"time":529000,"text":"I couldn't just stay in Seattle and raise my kids"},{"time":533000,"text":"in an upper-middle class neighborhood and feel good about it."},{"time":537000,"text":"This was not the world that I'd want my children to grow up in."},{"time":543000,"text":"So I decided to get engaged, and the first thing that I did"},{"time":547000,"text":"was to come back to Ghana and talk with a lot of people"},{"time":551000,"text":"and really try to understand what the real issues were."},{"time":555000,"text":"And three things kept coming up for every problem:"},{"time":560000,"text":"corruption, weak institutions"},{"time":563000,"text":"and the people who run them -- the leaders."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567000,"text":"Now, I was a little scared"},{"time":569000,"text":"because when you see those three problems,"},{"time":571000,"text":"they seem really hard to deal with."},{"time":574000,"text":"And they might say, \"Look, don't even try.\""},{"time":576000,"text":"But, for me, I asked the question,"},{"time":579000,"text":"\"Well, where are these leaders coming from?"},{"time":583000,"text":"What is it about Ghana that produces leaders"},{"time":587000,"text":"that are unethical or unable to solve problems?\""},{"time":591000,"text":"So I went to look at what was happening in our educational system."},{"time":594000,"text":"And it was the same -- learning by rote --"},{"time":596000,"text":"from primary school through graduate school."},{"time":600000,"text":"Very little emphasis on ethics,"},{"time":605000,"text":"and the typical graduate"},{"time":609000,"text":"from a university in Ghana has a stronger sense"},{"time":613000,"text":"of entitlement than a sense of responsibility."},{"time":617000,"text":"This is wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619000,"text":"So I decided to engage this particular problem."},{"time":624000,"text":"Because it seems to me that every society, every society,"},{"time":630000,"text":"must be very intentional about how it trains its leaders."},{"time":634000,"text":"And Ghana was not paying enough attention."},{"time":637000,"text":"And this is true across sub-Saharan Africa, actually."},{"time":644000,"text":"So this is what I'm doing now."},{"time":646000,"text":"I'm trying to bring the experience that I had at Swarthmore to Africa."},{"time":653000,"text":"I wish there was a liberal arts college in every African country."},{"time":657000,"text":"I think it would make a huge difference."},{"time":660000,"text":"And what Ashesi University is trying to do"},{"time":665000,"text":"is to train a new generation of ethical, entrepreneurial leaders."},{"time":672000,"text":"We're trying to train leaders of exceptional integrity,"},{"time":676000,"text":"who have the ability to confront the complex problems,"},{"time":679000,"text":"ask the right questions, and come up with workable solutions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":684000,"text":"I'll admit that there are times when it seems like \"Mission: Impossible,\""},{"time":691000,"text":"but we must believe that these kids are smart."},{"time":695000,"text":"That if we involve them in their education,"},{"time":698000,"text":"if we have them discuss the real issues that they confront --"},{"time":702000,"text":"that our whole society confronts --"},{"time":705000,"text":"and if we give them skills that enable them to engage the real world,"},{"time":711000,"text":"that magic will happen."},{"time":716000,"text":"Now, a month into this project, we'd just started classes."},{"time":724000,"text":"And a month into it, I come to the office,"},{"time":727000,"text":"and I have this email from one of our students."},{"time":730000,"text":"And it said, very simply, \"I am thinking now.\""},{"time":735000,"text":"And he signs off, \"Thank you.\""},{"time":740000,"text":"It's such a simple statement."},{"time":743000,"text":"But I was moved almost to tears"},{"time":745000,"text":"because I understood what was happening to this young man."},{"time":750000,"text":"And it is an awesome thing to be a part"},{"time":754000,"text":"of empowering someone in this way."},{"time":759000,"text":"I am thinking now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":763000,"text":"This year we challenged our students"},{"time":767000,"text":"to craft an honor code themselves."},{"time":770000,"text":"There's a very vibrant debate going on on campus now"},{"time":773000,"text":"over whether they should have an honor code,"},{"time":776000,"text":"and if so, what it should look like."},{"time":779000,"text":"One of the students asked a question that just warmed my heart."},{"time":783000,"text":"Can we create a perfect society?"},{"time":789000,"text":"Her understanding that a student-crafted honor code"},{"time":795000,"text":"constitutes a reach towards perfection is incredible."},{"time":801000,"text":"Now, we cannot achieve perfection,"},{"time":803000,"text":"but if we reach for it, then we can achieve excellence."},{"time":809000,"text":"I don't know ultimately what they will do."},{"time":811000,"text":"I don't know whether they will decide to have this honor code."},{"time":815000,"text":"But the conversation they're having now --"},{"time":817000,"text":"about what their good society should look like,"},{"time":821000,"text":"what their excellent society should look like,"},{"time":824000,"text":"is a really good thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":830000,"text":"Am I out of time? OK."},{"time":836000,"text":"Now, I just wanted to leave that slide up"},{"time":842000,"text":"because it's important that we think about it."},{"time":845000,"text":"I'm very excited about the fact"},{"time":848000,"text":"that every student at Ashesi University does community service before they graduate."},{"time":854000,"text":"That for many of them, it has been a life-altering experience."},{"time":859000,"text":"These young future leaders are beginning to understand"},{"time":867000,"text":"the real business of leadership,"},{"time":869000,"text":"the real privilege of leadership,"},{"time":871000,"text":"which is after all to serve humanity."},{"time":876000,"text":"I am even more thrilled by the fact that least year"},{"time":881000,"text":"our student body elected a woman"},{"time":883000,"text":"to be the head of Student Government."},{"time":887000,"text":"It's the first time in the history of Ghana"},{"time":890000,"text":"that a woman has been elected head of Student Government"},{"time":894000,"text":"at any university."},{"time":897000,"text":"It says a lot about her."},{"time":899000,"text":"It says a lot about the culture that's forming on campus."},{"time":904000,"text":"It says a lot about her peers who elected her."},{"time":907000,"text":"She won with 75 percent of the vote."}]},{"cues":[{"time":913000,"text":"And it gives me a lot of hope."},{"time":916000,"text":"It turns out that corporate West Africa"},{"time":919000,"text":"also appreciates what's happening with our students."},{"time":923000,"text":"We've graduated two classes of students to date."},{"time":927000,"text":"And every single one of them has been placed."},{"time":930000,"text":"And we're getting great reports back"},{"time":932000,"text":"from corporate Ghana, corporate West Africa,"},{"time":936000,"text":"and the things that they're most impressed about is work ethic."},{"time":941000,"text":"You know, that passion for what they're doing."},{"time":945000,"text":"The persistence, their ability to deal with ambiguity,"},{"time":949000,"text":"their ability to tackle problems that they haven't seen before."},{"time":955000,"text":"This is good because"},{"time":959000,"text":"over the past five years, there have been times"},{"time":962000,"text":"when I've felt this is \"Mission: Impossible.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":965000,"text":"And it's just wonderful to see these glimmers"},{"time":968000,"text":"of the promise of what can happen if we train our kids right."},{"time":975000,"text":"I think that the current and future leaders of Africa"},{"time":979000,"text":"have an incredible opportunity"},{"time":982000,"text":"to drive a major renaissance on the continent."},{"time":985000,"text":"It's an incredible opportunity."},{"time":987000,"text":"There aren't very many more opportunities like this in the world."},{"time":991000,"text":"I believe that Africa has reached an inflection point"},{"time":999000,"text":"with a march of democracy and free markets across the continent."},{"time":1003000,"text":"We have reached a moment from which can emerge"},{"time":1006000,"text":"a great society within one generation."},{"time":1010000,"text":"It will depend on inspired leadership."},{"time":1015000,"text":"And it is my contention that the manner in which we train our leaders"},{"time":1021000,"text":"will make all the difference."},{"time":1022000,"text":"Thank you, and God bless."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1024000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}